<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,721,928]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
REMARKS.—The species was recently reassigned to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sanborn" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[756,852,721,747]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Guyalna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[756,852,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Guyalna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on multiple diagnostic structures (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F." pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref73788" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2018 c) The cicadas (Hemiptera: Cicadidae) of Panama including the description of six new species, three new combinations, one new synonymy, and nine new records. Zootaxa, 4493 (1), 1 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4493.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Sanborn 2018c</bibRefCitation>
). It has a distinctive green head and thorax marked with piceous and a piceous abdomen possessing lateral silvery pile on tergites 3 and 4. It can be distinguished from the other Ecuadorian species of the genus by its size and orange basal area of the wings. Body lengths are 
<quantity box="[702,826,829,856]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="21.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="20.0">20–22 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,721,928]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
DISTRIBUTION.—The species has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[799,909,865,891]" name="Colombia" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[968,1061,865,891]" name="Ecuador" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[1078,1248,865,891]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 585" refId="ref71633" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i-vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; Sanborn 2013). The species has been reported from Cachabi, 
<collectingRegion box="[661,895,901,927]" country="Ecuador" name="Esmeraldas" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Esmeraldas province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[910,1073,901,928]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="304 - 319" refId="ref69306" refString="Distant, W. L. (1905 d) Rhynchotal notes XXX. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 7, 15, 304 - 319. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03745480509443047" type="journal article" year="1905">Distant 1905d</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Goding, F. W." box="[1084,1235,901,928]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref70044" refString="Goding, F. W. (1925) Synopsis of the Cicadidae of Ecuador. Revista del Colegio Nacional Rocafuerte, 7, 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1925">Goding 1925</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
